{"url": "https://www.balls.ie/olympics/south-korea-north-korea-opening-ceremony-605960", "uid": "balls.ie-olympics-south-korea-north-korea-opening-ceremony-605960", "images": ["https://www.balls.ie/images/facebook-black.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/twitter-x-black.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/youtube-black.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/logo.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/search.svg", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-0-0-menu.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-0-0-menu.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-forced-to-apologise-after-embarrassing-south-korea-opening-ceremony-gaffe.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-harrington", "https://www.balls.ie/images/facebook-color.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/linkedin-color.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/email-color.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/whatsapp-color.svg", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-forced-to-apologise-after-embarrassing-south-korea-opening-ceremony-gaffe.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-for-reaction-as-2026-electric-ireland-gaa-higher-education-draws-confirmed.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-harrington", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-for-ireland-set-to-finally-learn-their-fate-in-2027-rugby-world-cup-draw.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-connaughton", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-for-jacques-nienaber-clears-the-air-on-springboks-comments-and-reaffirms-commitment-to-lei.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-lydon", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-november-2025-republic-of-ireland-goalkeeper-caoimhin-kelleher-during-the-fifa-world-cup-2026.jpg", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-adeleke-039-s-irish-teammates-issue-stern-response-to-sonia-o-039-sullivan-criticism.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-medals-for-ireland-a-county-by-county-breakdown.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-dodge", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-mawdsley-topped-off-mad-tipperary-all-ireland-celebrations-by-racing-lads-in-the-street.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-wiffen-reveals-infamous-kneecap-impersonator-landed-him-in-hot-water-with-coach.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-bell-curran", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-mawdsley-issues-encouraging-update-on-extent-of-injury.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-wiffen-issues-statement-saying-he-wasn-039-t-man-in-balaclava-on-stage-at-kneecap-gig.png", "https://img.resized.co/balls_-mahoney", "https://www.balls.ie/images/facebook-white.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/twitter-x-white.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/youtube-white.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/apple-white.svg", "https://www.balls.ie/images/google-play-white.svg"], "publication-date": "", "text": "The opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympics was long, rain-sodden, but ultimately a brilliant spectacle along the banks of the River Seine.\n\nBoats brought the athletes down the river to replace the traditional parade around the Olympic Stadium, and the organisers interweaved artistic scenes between the introduction of each country's athletes.\n\nRecommended\n\nIt was innovative in many ways but perhaps most impressive was the manner in which the organisers broke up what can often be a long and tedious parade, as over 200 countries slowly enter the Olympic Stadium.\n\nThough it was largely a hugely successful opening ceremony, there was an embarrassing gaffe, as the South Korean delegation were mistakenly introduced under the name of North Korea.\n\nREAD HERE:Paris 2024 - The Irish In Action On Day One Of The Olympics\n\nREAD HERE:Surreal Mistake From Australian Diver Gifts Team GB First Olympics Medal\n\nAs the South Korean team (officially known as the 'People's Republic of Korea') were introduced to viewers around the world on Friday evening, both the official French and English announcers introduced them as the 'Democratic People's Republic of Korea.'\n\nThe subtitle on the TV world feed gave South Korea their correct title, while North Korea were correctly introduced later in the parade.\n\nThose up to date with their intricacies here will know that 'DPR Korea' is the official name of North Korea. There have been intense diplomatic tensions between North and South Korea ever since the armistice of the Korean War in 1953. There has been a partition on the Korean peninsula ever since, and tensions have only escalated in recent times.\n\nOf course, the International Olympic Committee would have hoped not to erroneously introduce any of the 205 nations participating in the Paris 2024 Olympics. However, given the ongoing deep tensions between the two parts of the Korean peninsula, this was a mistake the organisers would have especially hoped to avoid.\n\nThe IOC have been forced to apologise, after the South Korean president Yoon Suk Yeol urged IOC president Thomas Bach to ensure no further mistakes of this nature were made.\n\nAccording to theKorea Times, Yoon and Bach have spoken over the phone, with Bach apologising and Yoon saying that the people of South Korea were \"baffled\" by the huge error.\n\nIn a post on their Korean language Twitter account, the IOC said, \"We would like to offer a deep apology over the mistake that occurred in the introduction of the South Korean delegation during the opening ceremony.\"\n\nThe South Korean delegation had previously expressed its intention to raise the issue with France on a \"government level.\"\n\nAs innocent mistakes go, this is one of the worst we can remember in recent times.\n\n\n\n\n\nProcessing your request...\n\nYou are now subscribed!\n\n\n\nCopyright © 2025. All rights reserved. Developed bySquare1and powered byPublisherPlus.com", "title": "IOC Forced To Apologise After Embarrassing South Korea Gaffe | Balls.ie", "top-image": "https://www.balls.ie/images/facebook-black.svg", "domain": "www.balls.ie", "lang": "en", "author": "Eoin Harrington", "description": "The IOC have been forced to apologise after South Korea were accidentally introduced as \"DPR Korea\" at the Olympics opening ceremony", "keywords": "South Korea"}